# Data Format Rules for Minimalist Spanish Anchor App

When creating or modifying curriculum data in the `data/` directory, always follow these strict structure and tokenization rules.

## 1. Topic & Lesson Structure
- All topic files must append their data to the global array: 
  `window.AnchorData.push({ id, title, description, legacy, lessons: [...] });`
- Make sure `window.AnchorData = window.AnchorData || [];` is atop the file.
- Set `legacy: false` for new topics, `legacy: true` for old format topics (like topics_core.js).
- Each `lesson` must contain an `id`, a `title`, and an array of `phrases` (exactly 6 phrases per lesson).
- **Exam Lessons**: Add `exam: true` and `phrases: []` — app.js auto-populates from sibling lessons at runtime.
- **Curriculum Pacing (5 Lessons per Group)**: 
  - Part A = Yo
  - Part B = Tú / Usted
  - Part C = Él / Ella
  - Part D = Nosotros
  - Part E = Ellos / Ellas / Ustedes
- **Layout Standards**: 
  - Ensure topic and lesson cards in the UI use a 5-column layout on desktop: `grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-5`.
  - Do NOT use extra descriptors in Russian for "Вы" (e.g. no "вежливо"), simply use "Вы", "Вам", "У вас".

## 2. Phrase Object Structure
Each phrase must contain exactly three required keys (`ru`, `es`, `tokens`) plus an optional `meta` object:
```javascript
{
  ru: "Я не плохой",
  es: "Yo no soy malo",
  tokens: [
    { text: "Yo", type: "subject" },
    { text: " ", type: "space" },
    { text: "no", type: "negation" },
    { text: " ", type: "space" },
    { text: "soy", type: "verb" },
    { text: " ", type: "space" },
    { text: "malo", type: "object" }
  ],
  meta: {
    id: "ser_pres_yo_neg_malo",
    lemma: "ser",
    person: "yo",
    polarity: "negative",
    tense: "present",
    tags: ["identity", "adjective"],
    confusable_with: "estar"
  }
}
```

## 3. Strict Tokenization Rules
- **Exact Match:** The concatenated `text` of all tokens must *exactly* match the `es` string.
- **Spaces are distinct:** Every space must be its own token: `{ text: " ", type: "space" }`.
- **Supported Grammatical Types:**
  - `subject` (Blue — Yo, Tú, Él, Nosotros)
  - `verb` (Red — soy, tengo, hago, etc.)
  - `negation` (Yellow — no)
  - `object` (Green — bueno, tiempo, a casa, etc.)
  - `space` (Invisible spacer)

## 4. Meta Object Schema
- `id`: Unique string. Pattern: `{lemma}_{tense}_{person}_{polarity}` or `{lemma}_{tense}_{person}_{polarity}_{object}`
- `lemma`: Base verb infinitive (e.g., "ser", "estar")
- `person`: `"yo"` | `"tu"` | `"usted"` | `"el"` | `"ella"` | `"nosotros"` | `"ellos"` | `"ellas"` | `"ustedes"`
- `polarity`: `"affirmative"` | `"negative"`
- `tense`: `"present"` | `"past"`
- `tags`: Array of grouping strings (e.g., `["identity", "adjective"]`)
- `confusable_with`: Lemma of a confusable verb, or `null`

## 5. Streak Targets
- Regular lessons: 24
- Final Exam lessons: 50
